Troubleshooting Common Issues
Issue 1: binwalk Extraction Fails
Problem: binwalk cannot extract certain filesystem types.

Solution:

# Install additional extraction tools
sudo apt install -y jefferson ubi-utils

# Try manual extraction with specific tools
binwalk --dd="squashfs:squashfs" firmware.bin
Issue 2: Permission Denied Errors
Problem: Cannot access extracted files due to permissions.

Solution:

# Fix permissions on extracted directory
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER _firmware.bin.extracted/
chmod -R u+r _firmware.bin.extracted/
Issue 3: Large Firmware Files
Problem: Analysis takes too long on large firmware files.

Solution:

# Limit extraction depth
binwalk -e --max-size=100MB firmware.bin

# Use specific signatures only
binwalk -e --signature filesystem firmware.bin
Issue 4: Missing Dependencies
Problem: Some extraction tools are not available.

Solution:

# Install comprehensive extraction toolkit
sudo apt install -y binwalk foremost sleuthkit afflib-tools ewf-tools

# For Python dependencies
pip3 install --user python-magic pycrypto
